Headless Kit's logic is split into three publishable packages. This keeps adapters, proxy logic, and type definitions reusable across different frontends.

## @headless/core

The core library providing backend adapters, HMAC signing, HTTP utilities, and token management.

### Installation

```bash
bun add @headless/core
```

### Sub-path Exports

```typescript
import { LaravelAdapter, SymfonyAdapter, NodeAdapter } from '@headless/core/adapters';
import { apiRequest, apiRequestJson, ApiException } from '@headless/core/http';
import { generateSignature, hashBody } from '@headless/core/security';
import { TOKEN_CONFIG, isTokenExpiredByTimestamp } from '@headless/core/services';
import { resolveBackend, getCookieNamesForBackend } from '@headless/core/auth';
```

### AuthAdapter Interface

Every backend adapter implements this interface:

```typescript
type AuthAdapter = {
  login(credentials: LoginRequest): Promise<AuthResponse>;
  register(data: RegisterRequest): Promise<AuthResponse>;
  logout(): Promise<void>;
  refresh(request?: RefreshTokenRequest): Promise<AuthResponse>;
  getUser(): Promise<NormalizedUser | null>;
  getOAuthProviders(): Promise<string[]>;
  getOAuthUrl(provider: string): Promise<string>;
  sendMagicLink?(email: string): Promise<void>;
  storeTokens(tokens: TokenStorage): Promise<void>;
  clearTokens(): Promise<void>;
  getAccessToken(): Promise<string | null>;
};
```

### CookieStore Interface

Adapters use a `CookieStore` abstraction for token persistence. This allows the same adapter logic to work in different environments (Next.js, Express, standalone):

```typescript
type CookieStore = {
  get(name: string): CookieValue | undefined | Promise<CookieValue | undefined>;
  set(options: CookieSetOptions & { name: string; value: string }): void | Promise<void>;
  delete(name: string): void | Promise<void>;
};
```

### BaseAdapter

All three adapters extend `BaseAdapter`, which handles:

- Token storage/retrieval via `CookieStore`
- Auth header injection (`Authorization: Bearer ...`)
- HTTP request execution via `apiRequestJson`
- Cookie configuration (HttpOnly, Secure, SameSite, path, maxAge)

```typescript
import { LaravelAdapter } from '@headless/core/adapters';

const adapter = new LaravelAdapter(
  {
    baseUrl: 'http://localhost:8000',
    secret: 'your-hmac-secret',
    bffId: 'nextjs-bff',
  },
  {
    cookieStore: myCookieStore,
    cookieNames: {
      accessToken: 'auth_token_laravel',
      refreshToken: 'refresh_token_laravel',
      tokenExpiresAt: 'token_expires_at_laravel',
    },
  }
);
```

### Transformers

Each adapter has a transformer module that normalizes backend-specific response formats into the shared `AuthResponse` / `NormalizedUser` types:

- `packages/core/src/adapters/laravel/transformer.ts`
- `packages/core/src/adapters/symfony/transformer.ts`
- `packages/core/src/adapters/node/transformer.ts`

